article.headline: English, hot start lead Iona to 83-67 win over Monmouth (NJ)

images.name: A. English made Three Point Jumper. Assisted by I. Muhammad.
images.caption: 1H (18:03) IONA A.J. English made Three Point Jumper. Assisted by Ibn Muhammad.

article.linkText: English, hot start lead Iona to 83-67 win over Monmouth (NJ)
article.story: WEST LONG BRANCH, N.J. -- A.J. English scored 31 and Iona led by as many as 21 in the first half before cruising to a 83-67 win over Monmouth (NJ) on Friday night. Aaron Rountree scored 13, Deyshonee Much added 11 and Jordan Washington had 10 points for Iona, which pulled to within a half-game of the Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference-leading Hawks. The Gaels (16-10, 13-4) scored 19 consecutive points, as Monmouth went scoreless for seven-plus minutes, to take a 15-point lead with eight minutes left in the first half. A 3 by Much gave Iona a 41-20 lead about four minutes later, the Gaels went into the break up by 19 and led by double figures throughout the second half. Justin Robinson led Monmouth (22-6, 14-3) with 21 points. The teams were involved in a scuffle following the Hawks' 110-102 win over Iona on Jan. 15 which resulted in a two-game suspension for Gaels' forward Jordan Washington.
